headline_main: Trump Gets ‘a Dose of His Own Medicine’ at NATO

abstract: Who gets to pick the next president of the United States — President Trump, Russia or us?
snippet: Who gets to pick the next president of the United States — President Trump, Russia or us?
lead_paragraph: The report released on Wednesday by the House Intelligence Committee begins with a powerful indictment: “The impeachment inquiry,” the first sentence says, “uncovered a monthslong effort by President Trump to use the powers of his office to solicit foreign interference on his behalf in the 2020 election.”

abstract: Hours after announcing that the House would begin drafting articles of impeachment, Speaker Nancy Pelosi said she regularly prayed for the president. President Trump said he didn’t believe her.
snippet: Hours after announcing that the House would begin drafting articles of impeachment, Speaker Nancy Pelosi said she regularly prayed for the president. President Trump said he didn’t believe her.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Speaker Nancy Pelosi lashed out in anger on Thursday at a reporter who asked whether she hated President Trump, prompting Mr. Trump to accuse her of having “a nervous fit.”

abstract: While e-cigarettes are still the most popular, teenagers are also smoking other items like cigarillos — another worrisome sign for nicotine addiction, the C.D.C. says.
snippet: While e-cigarettes are still the most popular, teenagers are also smoking other items like cigarillos — another worrisome sign for nicotine addiction, the C.D.C. says.
lead_paragraph: Nearly one in three high school students has reported using a tobacco product recently, according to a new federal survey released on Thursday, evidence that concerns over nicotine addiction among teenagers are not limited to e-cigarettes.

abstract: As the party reckons with the likelihood of an all-white candidate lineup for the December debate, Cory Booker and Julián Castro see fund-raising gains.
snippet: As the party reckons with the likelihood of an all-white candidate lineup for the December debate, Cory Booker and Julián Castro see fund-raising gains.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Senator Cory Booker strode onstage here with a question, one that voters, activists and disgruntled members of the Democratic National Committee are also asking in the wake of Senator Kamala Harris’s sudden departure from the 2020 race.

abstract: At least 151 pro-government forces and 63 civilians have been killed in Afghanistan so far this month.
snippet: At least 151 pro-government forces and 63 civilians have been killed in Afghanistan so far this month.
lead_paragraph: At least 40 pro-government forces and 23 civilians were killed in Afghanistan during the past week. The deadliest attack took place in Ghazni Province, where an insurgent who had infiltrated the Afghan army opened fire on his colleagues while they were sleeping, killing 23 soldiers and wounding another before seizing their weapons and rejoining the Taliban. In the Jaghatu District of the same province, a roadside bomb killed 10 civilians who were traveling by shuttle bus. Later in the week, another 10 civilians were killed by a roadside bomb in the Abo Khana area of Alisher District. Two women and three children were among those killed.

abstract: The justices will soon say whether they will hear the case, about a House subpoena, along with one concerning a subpoena from Manhattan prosecutors.
snippet: The justices will soon say whether they will hear the case, about a House subpoena, along with one concerning a subpoena from Manhattan prosecutors.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump asked the Supreme Court on Thursday to hear a second case concerning a subpoena to his accounting firm for his financial records. The new petition, objecting to a subpoena from a House committee, follows a petition filed last month about a similar subpoena from Manhattan prosecutors.

headline_main: ‘I Don’t Hate Anyone,’ Pelosi Tells Reporter After Trump Question

abstract: Shortly after John Kerry, the former secretary of state, endorsed Mr. Biden in the 2020 Democratic primary, the former vice president had a heated confrontation with a voter.
snippet: Shortly after John Kerry, the former secretary of state, endorsed Mr. Biden in the 2020 Democratic primary, the former vice president had a heated confrontation with a voter.
lead_paragraph: NEW HAMPTON, Iowa — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. on Thursday angrily lashed out at a voter who questioned his son’s overseas business dealings at a campaign stop in Iowa, calling the man a “damn liar” in an unusually heated exchange.
